<TEXT>
suspected paramilitary forces dragged three 
men from their homes and killed them and three people were slain 
in other attacks blamed on rebels police and witnesses said 
the craftsmen were taken from their homes friday by four men in 
military clothing and armed with assault rifles and revolvers in 
ayacucho a rebel stronghold about 230 miles southeast of lima 
according to a victims daughter 
the four men shot the victims in the head and fled said 
inocenta viga 
the incident occurred during an armyenforced curfew imposed 10 
days ago after the assassination of ayacuchos mayor by suspected 
maoist shining path rebels 
in the last year paramilitary death squads have appeared 
slaying suspected backers of the leftist shining path 
in another incident friday police said five shining path 
guerrillas entered a primary school in the jungle town of san 
martin de pangoa 160 miles east of lima and opened fire with 
submachine guns killing the schools principal and a teacher 
in the town of marcara 220 miles northeast of lima shining 
path rebels shot and killed an agronomist and wounded the towns 
former marxist mayor 
the government says more than 15000 people have died in 
insurgencyrelated violence since 1980 when the shining path 
launched its struggle against perus elected government 
