an emergency quarantine aimed at protecting 
the endangered desert tortoise goes into effect sunday closing 59 
square miles of the mojave desert to offroad enthusiasts hikers 
and grazing sheep 
were losing about 50 percent of the adult tortoises a year 
out there right now said lee delaney head of the federal bureau 
of land managements area office in ridgecrest if that 
continues it would be a few short years before we dont have a 
tortoise population 
blm workers and volunteers were out saturday ringing the area 
with signs to notify the public of the oneyear quarantine delaney 
