<TEXT>
house and senate negotiators are telling 
federal arts agencies not to give any money to obscene art but 
theyre backing away from stronger standards proposed by sen jesse 
helms 
under a compromise reached friday the national endowment for 
the arts and national endowment for the humanities would receive 
budgets in the 1990 fiscal year provided they implement new 
standards in giving grants 
the provision is a weakening of a senatepassed measure backed 
by helms rnc that called for banning federal aid for art that 
is obscene or indecent or that denigrates a religion race 
ethnic background age group or handicap 
instead grants would be denied to art that depicts 
sadomasochism homoeroticism the sexual exploitation of children 
or individuals engaged in the sex act 
</TEXT>
